# Int8 overflow tests

(tx 'create schema test')
(tx 'create table test.item(field: int8)')
!tx 'insert (9223372036854775808) into test.item (field)'
---
> error[PO0001]: value overflows column `field` type `INT8`
>   1 │ insert (9223372036854775808) into test.item (field)
>     │         ^
>     = value `9223372036854775808` does not fit into `INT8` (range: -9,223,372,036,854,775,808 to 9,223,372,036,854,775,807)
> 
> note: column `field` is of type `INT8`
> 
> help: reduce the value, change the column type to a wider type or change the overflow policy
